8 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
9 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-7-113 of Title 27A, unless
10 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
11 A. 1. The Oklahoma Conservation Commission shall undertake a
12 comprehensive watershed-based water quality plan designed to improve
13 and protect the water quality and aquatic habitat in the Spring
14 Creek watershed through the utilization of voluntary, incentive-
15 based programs.
16 2. On or before June 1, 2026, the Commission shall publish an
17 electronic report of the findings. The Commission may, from time to
18 time, update such findings as conditions change and pertinent
19 information becomes available.
20 B. The Commission may contract and cooperate with the Natural
21 Resources Conservation Service of the United States Department of
22 Agriculture and the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency to conduct
23 activities provided for in this section.
