4 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-7-114 of Title 27A, unless
6 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
8 for the Oklahoma Conservation Commission to be designated the
9 “Spring Creek Watershed Study Cash Fund Revolving Fund”. The fund
10 shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations,
11 and shall consist of all monies received by the Commission from
12 appropriations by the Legislature to the fund, and any money
13 received as gifts, grants, or other contributions from public or
14 private sources provided for the purpose of implementing the Spring
15 Creek Watershed Study Act. All monies accruing to the credit of the
16 fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the
17 Commission for the purpose provided for in this act. Expenditures
18 from the fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State
19 Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by law with the
20 Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise Services for
21 approval and payment.
22 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
